{"role": "user", "content": "User laminated-wire posted:\n\"@intense-copper, I have another question about quantum entanglement.\nIs it possible for entangled particles to have different properties,\nsuch as spin or polarization, and still remain entangled?\"\nUser intense-copper posted:\n\"@laminated-wire, yes, that's absolutely possible. Entangled particles can\nhave different properties, but their properties are still correlated.\nThis is known as the principle of complementarity.\"\nUser laminated-wire posted:\n\"Wow, that's fascinating. I'll have to read more about the principle of\ncomplementarity. Thank you for your help, @intense-copper.\"\nUser moderator posted:"}

